The paper deals with network embedding, which is a popular topic in machine learning and data mining. The focus of the paper is on learning in a dynamic environment, which involves the evolution of network structure and node attributes over time. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.SI is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with network analysis and modeling. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve machine learning, data mining, and software engineering techniques that are applicable to the problem of dynamic network embedding.
